main.name: Zedruu the Greathearted
main.oracle_text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, you gain X life and draw X cards, where X is the number of permanents you own that your opponents control.
{U}{R}{W}: Target opponent gains control of target permanent you control.

card.name: Arbiter of Knollridge
card.oracle_text:
Vigilance
When Arbiter of Knollridge enters, each player's life total becomes the highest life total among all players.
card.flavor_text: Though giants are mortal, they live so long and on such a grand scale that many small folk don't believe they ever truly die.

card.name: Armillary Sphere
card.oracle_text: {2}, {T}, Sacrifice Armillary Sphere: Search your library for up to two basic land cards, reveal them, put them into your hand, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: The mysterious purpose of two of the rings had eluded Esper mages—until now.

card.name: Austere Command
card.oracle_text:
Choose two —
• Destroy all artifacts.
• Destroy all enchantments.
• Destroy all creatures with mana value 3 or less.
• Destroy all creatures with mana value 4 or greater.

card.name: Azorius Chancery
card.oracle_text:
Azorius Chancery enters tapped.
When Azorius Chancery enters, return a land you control to its owner's hand.
{T}: Add {W}{U}.

card.name: Azorius Guildmage
card.oracle_text:
{2}{W}: Tap target creature.
{2}{U}: Counter target activated ability. (Mana abilities can't be targeted.)

card.name: Champion's Helm
Chaos Warp
card.oracle_text: The owner of target permanent shuffles it into their library, then reveals the top card of their library. If it's a permanent card, they put it onto the battlefield.

card.name: Breath of Darigaaz
card.oracle_text:
Kicker {2} (You may pay an additional {2} as you cast this spell.)
Breath of Darigaaz deals 1 damage to each creature without flying and each player. If this spell was kicked, it deals 4 damage to each creature without flying and each player instead.

card.name: Brion Stoutarm
card.oracle_text:
Lifelink
{R}, {T}, Sacrifice another creature: Brion Stoutarm deals damage equal to the sacrificed creature's power to target player or planeswalker.

card.name: Boros Garrison
card.oracle_text:
Boros Garrison enters tapped.
When Boros Garrison enters, return a land you control to its owner's hand.
{T}: Add {R}{W}.

card.name: Brainstorm
card.oracle_text: Draw three cards, then put two cards from your hand on top of your library in any order.
card.flavor_text:
"I see more than others do because I know where to look."
—Saprazzan vizier

card.name: Darksteel Ingot
card.oracle_text:
Indestructible (Effects that say "destroy" don't destroy this artifact.)
{T}: Add one mana of any color.

card.name: Chromeshell Crab
card.oracle_text:
Morph {4}{U} (You may cast this card face down as a 2/2 creature for {3}. Turn it face up any time for its morph cost.)
When Chromeshell Crab is turned face up, you may exchange control of target creature you control and target creature an opponent controls.

card.name: Command Tower
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text: When defeat is near and guidance is scarce, all eyes look in one direction.

card.name: Court Hussar
card.oracle_text:
Vigilance
When Court Hussar enters, look at the top three cards of your library, then put one of them into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.
When Court Hussar enters, sacrifice it unless {W} was spent to cast it.

card.name: Crescendo of War
card.oracle_text:
At the beginning of each upkeep, put a strife counter on Crescendo of War.
Attacking creatures get +1/+0 for each strife counter on Crescendo of War.
Blocking creatures you control get +1/+0 for each strife counter on Crescendo of War.

card.name: Death by Dragons
card.oracle_text: Each player other than target player creates a 5/5 red Dragon creature token with flying.
card.flavor_text: Suddenly, Eldo felt very alone.

card.name: Dominus of Fealty
card.oracle_text:
Flying
At the beginning of your upkeep, you may gain control of target permanent until end of turn. If you do, untap it and it gains haste until end of turn.
card.flavor_text:
"Nothing is truly your own. It is his, whether you know it or not."
—*The Seer's Parables*

card.name: Dreamstone Hedron
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}{C}{C}.
{3}, {T}, Sacrifice Dreamstone Hedron: Draw three cards.
card.flavor_text: Only the Eldrazi mind thinks in the warped paths required to open the hedrons and tap the power within.

card.name: False Prophet
card.oracle_text: When False Prophet dies, exile all creatures.
card.flavor_text: "You lived for Serra's love. Will you not die for it?"

card.name: Fellwar Stone
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color that a land an opponent controls could produce.
card.flavor_text:
"What do you have that I cannot obtain?"
—Mairsil, the Pretender

card.name: Evolving Wilds
card.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Evolving Wilds: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Every world is an organism, able to grow new lands. Some just do it faster than others.

card.name: Flametongue Kavu
card.oracle_text: When Flametongue Kavu enters, it deals 4 damage to target creature.
card.flavor_text:
"For dim-witted, thick-skulled genetic mutants, they have pretty good aim."
—Sisay, captain of the *Weatherlight*

card.name: Flusterstorm
card.oracle_text:
Counter target instant or sorcery spell unless its controller pays {1}.
Storm (When you cast this spell, copy it for each spell cast before it this turn. You may choose new targets for the copies.)

card.name: Fog Bank
card.oracle_text:
Defender, flying
Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt to and dealt by Fog Bank.

card.name: Guard Gomazoa
card.oracle_text:
Defender, flying
Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt to Guard Gomazoa.
card.flavor_text: It lingers near the outposts of the Makindi Trenches, inadvertently granting another layer of defense.

card.name: Goblin Cadets
card.oracle_text: Whenever Goblin Cadets blocks or becomes blocked, target opponent gains control of it. (This removes Goblin Cadets from combat.)
card.flavor_text: "If you kids don't stop that racket, I'm turning this expedition around *right now!*"

card.name: Ghostly Prison
card.oracle_text: Creatures can't attack you unless their controller pays {2} for each creature they control that's attacking you.
card.flavor_text:
"May the memory of our fallen heroes ensnare the violent hearts of lesser men."
—Great Threshold of Monserkat inscription

card.name: Gomazoa
card.oracle_text:
Defender, flying
{T}: Put Gomazoa and each creature it's blocking on top of their owners' libraries, then those players shuffle.
card.flavor_text: To explorers, "point man" is a polite way of saying "gomazoa fodder."

card.name: Insurrection
card.oracle_text: Untap all creatures and gain control of them until end of turn. They gain haste until end of turn.
card.flavor_text:
"Maybe they wanted to be on the winning side for once."
—Matoc, lavamancer

card.name: Izzet Boilerworks
card.oracle_text:
Izzet Boilerworks enters tapped.
When Izzet Boilerworks enters, return a land you control to its owner's hand.
{T}: Add {U}{R}.

card.name: Izzet Chronarch
card.oracle_text: When Izzet Chronarch enters, return target instant or sorcery card from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text: He ensures not only whether but also when and where the lightning strikes twice.

card.name: Howling Mine
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of each player's draw step, if Howling Mine is untapped, that player draws an additional card.
card.flavor_text: The mine's riches never end, nor do the moans of the spirits doomed to haunt them.

card.name: Lightning Greaves
card.oracle_text:
Equipped creature has haste and shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
Equip {0}
card.flavor_text: After lightning struck the cliffs, the ore became iron, the iron became steel, and the steel became greaves. The lightning never left.

card.name: Jötun Grunt
card.oracle_text: Cumulative upkeep—Put two cards from a single graveyard on the bottom of their owner's library. (At the beginning of your upkeep, put an age counter on this permanent, then sacrifice it unless you pay its upkeep cost for each age counter on it.)

card.name: Journey to Nowhere
card.oracle_text:
When Journey to Nowhere enters, exile target creature.
When Journey to Nowhere leaves the battlefield, return the exiled card to the battlefield under its owner's control.

card.name: Lash Out
card.oracle_text: Lash Out deals 3 damage to target creature. Clash with an opponent. If you win, Lash Out deals 3 damage to that creature's controller. (Each clashing player reveals the top card of their library, then puts that card on the top or bottom. A player wins if their card had a higher mana value.)

card.name: Martyr's Bond
card.oracle_text: Whenever Martyr's Bond or another nonland permanent you control is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, each opponent sacrifices a permanent that shares a card type with it.
card.flavor_text:
"Our lives are connected by divine law. The truth of this will be made evident in time."
—Zedruu the Greathearted

card.name: Murmurs from Beyond
card.oracle_text: Reveal the top three cards of your library. An opponent chooses one of them. Put that card into your graveyard and the rest into your hand.
card.flavor_text: Like pools of fog that hid treacherous rocks from sailors' eyes, so too were the hands of the kami.

card.name: Nin, the Pain Artist
card.oracle_text: {X}{U}{R}, {T}: Nin, the Pain Artist deals X damage to target creature. That creature's controller draws X cards.
card.flavor_text: "Your body is a delicate instrument that tells me truths. These devices help me 'tune' that instrument."

card.name: Numot, the Devastator
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever Numot, the Devastator deals combat damage to a player, you may pay {2}{R}. If you do, destroy up to two target lands.

card.name: Oblation
card.oracle_text: The owner of target nonland permanent shuffles it into their library, then draws two cards.
card.flavor_text: "A richer people could give more but they could never give as much."

card.name: Propaganda
card.oracle_text: Creatures can't attack you unless their controller pays {2} for each creature they control that's attacking you.
card.flavor_text:
"You've failed Gerrard. You've failed the Legacy. You've failed yourself. I can do no more."
—Volrath, to Karn

card.name: Pollen Lullaby
card.oracle_text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt this turn. Clash with an opponent. If you win, creatures that player controls don't untap during the player's next untap step. (Each clashing player reveals the top card of their library, then puts that card on the top or bottom. A player wins if their card had a higher mana value.)

card.name: Perilous Research
card.oracle_text: Draw two cards, then sacrifice a permanent.
card.flavor_text: When the School of the Unseen fell, so many magical treasures lay abandoned that no amount of death could deter the stream of thieves and desperate scholars.

card.name: Prison Term
card.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature can't attack or block, and its activated abilities can't be activated.
Whenever a creature an opponent controls enters, you may attach Prison Term to that creature.

card.name: Prophetic Prism
card.oracle_text:
When Prophetic Prism enters, draw a card.
{1}, {T}: Add one mana of any color.
card.flavor_text: "The explorer who found it got a bad deal when he sold it. He merely got rich."

card.name: Plumeveil
card.oracle_text:
Flash
Defender, flying
card.flavor_text:
"It was vast, a great sheet of soaring wings, and equally silent. It caught us unawares and blocked our view of the kithkin stronghold."
—Grensch, merrow cutthroat

card.name: Rapacious One
card.oracle_text:
Trample
Whenever Rapacious One deals combat damage to a player, create that many 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature tokens. They have "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C}."

card.name: Reins of Power
card.oracle_text: Untap all creatures you control and all creatures target opponent controls. You and that opponent each gain control of all creatures the other controls until end of turn. Those creatures gain haste until end of turn.

card.name: Repulse
card.oracle_text:
Return target creature to its owner's hand.
Draw a card.
card.flavor_text: "You aren't invited."

card.name: Punishing Fire
card.oracle_text:
Punishing Fire deals 2 damage to any target.
Whenever an opponent gains life, you may pay {R}. If you do, return Punishing Fire from your graveyard to your hand.

card.name: Scattering Stroke
card.oracle_text: Counter target spell. Clash with an opponent. If you win, at the beginning of your next main phase, you may add an amount of {C} equal to that spell's mana value. (Each clashing player reveals the top card of their library, then puts that card on the top or bottom. A player wins if their card had a higher mana value.)

card.name: Ruhan of the Fomori
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of combat on your turn, choose an opponent at random. Ruhan of the Fomori attacks that player this combat if able.
card.flavor_text: Unfettered by allegiance, driven by war.

card.name: Spell Crumple
card.oracle_text: Counter target spell. If that spell is countered this way, put it on the bottom of its owner's library instead of into that player's graveyard. Put Spell Crumple on the bottom of its owner's library.

card.name: Sol Ring
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text: Lost to time is the artificer's art of trapping light from a distant star in a ring of purest gold.

card.name: Soul Snare
card.oracle_text: {W}, Sacrifice Soul Snare: Exile target creature that's attacking you or a planeswalker you control.
card.flavor_text:
"Body and spirit are sworn enemies. They will take any excuse to be rid of each other."
—Tariel, Reckoner of Souls

card.name: Skyscribing
card.oracle_text:
Each player draws X cards.
Forecast — {2}{U}, Reveal Skyscribing from your hand: Each player draws a card. (Activate only during your upkeep and only once each turn.)

card.name: Spurnmage Advocate
card.oracle_text: {T}: Return two target cards from an opponent's graveyard to their hand. Destroy target attacking creature.
card.flavor_text: "Our unity humbles our foes."

card.name: Trade Secrets
card.oracle_text: Target opponent draws two cards, then you draw up to four cards. That opponent may repeat this process as many times as they choose.

card.name: Terramorphic Expanse
card.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Terramorphic Expanse: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Take two steps north into the unsettled future, south into the unquiet past, east into the present day, or west into the great unknown.

card.name: Vision Skeins
card.oracle_text: Each player draws two cards.
card.flavor_text: "I could see in the other mage's eyes that he'd thought of it too. Then it became a race to exploit the knowledge first."

card.name: Vedalken Plotter
card.oracle_text: When Vedalken Plotter enters, exchange control of target land you control and target land an opponent controls.
card.flavor_text: "Fair? At what point in our negotiations did you convince yourself my goal was to be fair?"

card.name: Vow of Flight
card.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +2/+2, has flying, and can't attack you or planeswalkers you control.
card.flavor_text:
"Soaring is wasted on the winged."
—Edric, Spymaster of Trest

card.name: Vow of Lightning
card.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +2/+2, has first strike, and can't attack you or planeswalkers you control.
card.flavor_text:
"Ruhan would never agree to such terms."
—Ruhan of the Fomori

card.name: Vow of Duty
card.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +2/+2, has vigilance, and can't attack you or planeswalkers you control.
card.flavor_text:
"I prefer loyalty to be a matter of respect, not of magic. But one does what one must."
—Kaalia of the Vast

card.name: Windborn Muse
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Creatures can't attack you unless their controller pays {2} for each creature they control that's attacking you.
card.flavor_text:
"Her voice is justice, clear and relentless."
—Akroma, angelic avenger

card.name: Wall of Omens
card.oracle_text:
Defender
When Wall of Omens enters, draw a card.
card.flavor_text:
"I search for a vision of Zendikar that does not include the Eldrazi."
—Expedition journal entry

card.name: Wild Ricochet
card.oracle_text: You may choose new targets for target instant or sorcery spell. Then copy that spell. You may choose new targets for the copy.
card.flavor_text: "I knew that trick long before your great-grandmother's great-grandmother was born."

card.name: Wall of Denial
card.oracle_text:
Defender, flying
Shroud (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
card.flavor_text: It provides what every discerning mage requires—time to think.

card.name: Whirlpool Whelm
card.oracle_text: Clash with an opponent, then return target creature to its owner's hand. If you win, you may put that creature on top of its owner's library instead. (Each clashing player reveals the top card of their library, then puts that card on the top or bottom. A player wins if their card had a higher mana value.)
